commands

TO list the docker images locally > docker image ls

To build the image from source code, go into source code directory (docker image build -t vmuslapuram07131/first_container:Img .)

To push the Built container Image to Docker Hub registry >> docker image push vmuslapuram07131/first_container:Img

run docker and map port >docker container run -d --name web -p 8000:8080 vmuslapuram07131/first_container:Img

docker container list > docker contain -ls -a

Docker Stop > docker container stop web 

Docker Start> docker container stop web(Name you used in line 12) 

delete docker container > docker container rm web



docker-compose --version

To Launch Docker Containers with docker compose File
            -navigate to docker compose yml file location >>>docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml up 

to bring containers down docker compose >>> docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml down
